Barry Bateman joins us now for the latest on this. #eNCA #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - A criminal case was lodged against the national police commissioner on 9 December coming from the Independent Police Investigative Directorate. IPID says Police Commissioner Khehla Sitole has failed to cooperate with the investigation into the murder of Charl Kinnear. The Anti-Gang Unit detective was gunned down in 2020. READ: Kinnear killing | Modack, Kilian back in the dock A court has already found Sitole guilty of breaching his duties. President Cyril Ramaphosa announced his intention to suspend Sitole back in October. He remains in charge of the South African Police Service. READ: Sitole unfit for office - Ipusa The Police Ministry confirmed it has received the information on the charges from IPID. It says the letter will be referred to the president. Meanwhile, IPID says the letter to the minister was confidential and condemned the leak. Police watchdog, IPID, has registered a criminal case against National Police Commissioner Khehla Sitole for not cooperating with the investigation into the murder of police officer Charl Kinnear. eNCA's Thulasizwe Simelane spoke with Nicolette Kinnear, Kinnear's wife. Courtesy of #DStv403